Class ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestListBroadcastIntent

java.lang.Object
  com.dsi.ant.plugins.ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestListBroadcastIntent
Enclosing class:
ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices
public class ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestListBroadcastIntent
extends java.lang.Object

This broadcast intent will be sent when the search is requesting available devices to connect to. A third party subscriber seeking to provide access to devices should subscribe a BroadcastReceiver to receive this intent. If the information in this intent is applicable to the devices provided by the third party, then a ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestList_ResponseMessage with a list of the available devices can be returned through the PARAM_msgrDEVLISTRECEIVER messenger.

ACTION_REQLIST_RXONLY

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_REQLIST_RXONLY
The action for this intent for receivers to subscribe to. The RXONLY request means that the provided device does not need to support any ANT commands, only forward AntMessages and state changes to the client.

PARAM_bundleANTDEVICEPARAMS

public static final java.lang.String PARAM_bundleANTDEVICEPARAMS
Key to the bundle containing the device parameter information of the device(s) the client is requesting. Any devices matching these parameters can be returned in the (@link RequestAccess_ResponseMessage}. Note: For this request for the ANT Channel Device ID a wildcard value of 0 indicates the client is requesting all device IDs, any other value indicates the client is only looking for the device with that specific ID.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

PARAM_intREQID

public static final java.lang.String PARAM_intREQID
Key to the REQID in the request info bundle. The REQID is an integer token identified with this request, it is used to associate requests with responses. All ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestList_ResponseMessage sent as a response to this REQID must have a matching REQID. Apart from the values matching, the specific numerical value has no meaning and will be different between requests.

PARAM_stringREQUESTERDISPLAYNAME

public static final java.lang.String PARAM_stringREQUESTERDISPLAYNAME
Key to a display friendly name of the requester. The requester includes this value to allow the provider to display the source of the request. Note: The client may or may not be the same as the requester. The 'client' refers to the code that is utilizing the device. For example, if a heart rate graphing application is using the ANT+ Heart Rate plugin to get data, the graphing application is the client, but the ANT+ plugin is the requester because it will perform the actual request on behalf of the client.
